1	// Section 9 redesign guard: a narrow QEMU-virt RAM region [0x80000000, ...)
2	// over an mmap-backed external buffer must (a) not trip SimpleMemory's
3	// size-check, and (b) translate GPA 0x80010000 to file offset 0x10000 so
4	// QEMU and vsim see identical bytes through the same backing file.
5	//
6	// On the original wide region [RAM_BASE=0, RAM_END=0x8FFFFFFF] this same
7	// 8 MB external_buffer would be rejected by SimpleMemory's owned_size()
8	// check (8 MB < ~2.25 GB), so this test only compiles + passes after the
9	// "structural: parameterize Platform RAM region for shared-mem mode"
10	// commit lands and the buffer/region are sized to match.
